<p>Today I take your calls on gardening, disaster relief, firearms, energy, foreign languages, moving, &#8220;job security&#8221;  and more.</p>
<p>Remember to be on a show like this one just pick up your phone and call <strong><span style="color: #800000;">866-65-THINK</span></strong>. The best way to improve your chances of being on the air is ask your question or make your point up front, then provide details.</p>
<p>Also please do your best to call from a quite area with a good connection and speak up so you can be well heard. I can’t put all calls on the air but I do my best to get most of them on.</p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #800000;">Join Me Today As I Respond to Your Calls and Discuss&#8230;</span></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The best way to prep ground for a new garden</li>
<li>Why people with &#8220;no sympathy&#8221; for victims are mentally defective</li>
<li>Expert council member &#8220;Joe Nobody&#8221; weighs in on rifle stances</li>
<li>Steven Harris on modified vs. true sine wave inverters</li>
<li>How hunters might develop <a target="_blank" title="permaculture" href="http://tspwiki.com/index.php?title=Permaculture">permaculture</a> style food plots</li>
<li><a target="_blank" title="Paul Wheaton" href="http://tspwiki.com/index.php?title=Paul_Wheaton">Paul Wheaton</a> weighs in on best practices for potato production</li>
<li>Why banks are 100% unmotivated in selling foreclosed properties</li>
<li>Why Russian may be one of the best foreign languages to learn today</li>
<li>Growing peas for long term storage</li>
<li>Thoughts on moving and weighing options</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><span style="color: #800000;">Resources for today’s show…</span></strong></p>
